  "guideTitle": "ICF Guide",
  "guideWhatIsIcf": "What is the ICF?",
  "guideWhatIsIcfText": "The ICF (International Classification of Functioning, Disability and Health) is the WHO's international classification for describing health and health-related states. It provides a unified language and framework for describing functioning, disability and health.\n\nUnlike the ICD (International Classification of Diseases), which classifies diagnoses, the ICF describes the impact of health conditions on a person's daily life.",
  "guideWhatFor": "What is the ICF used for?",
  "guideWhatForText": "The ICF is used in many areas of health and social services:",
  "guideUse1": "Rehabilitation: Documenting functional limitations and therapy goals",
  "guideUse2": "Social medicine: Assessing participation restrictions",
  "guideUse3": "Care: Evaluating support needs",
  "guideUse4": "Research: Comparable description of health conditions",
  "guideUse5": "Health policy: Planning and evaluating healthcare services",
  "guideStructure": "Structure of the ICF",
  "guideStructureText": "The ICF is organized into four domains. Each domain has chapters, categories and sub-categories:",
  "guideDomainB": "Physiological and psychological body functions",
  "guideDomainS": "Anatomical parts of the body (organs, limbs)",
  "guideDomainD": "Execution of tasks and actions in daily life",
  "guideDomainE": "Physical, social and attitudinal environment",
  "guideHowToRead": "How to read an ICF code?",
  "guideHowToReadText": "Each ICF code consists of a letter (domain) and digits (chapter, category, sub-category):",
  "guideDomain": "Domain",
  "guideChapter": "Chapter",
  "guideCategory": "Category",
  "guideSubCategory": "Sub-cat.",
  "guideCodeExample": "b1140 = Orientation to time\n(b = Body Functions, 1 = Mental Functions,\n14 = Orientation, 0 = to time)",
  "guideQualifiers": "Qualifiers",
  "guideQualifiersText": "Qualifiers indicate the severity of a problem. They are appended to the code with a dot:",
  "guideQualifierExample": "Example:",
  "guideQualifierExampleDesc": "Mobility of joint functions (b710)\nwith moderate problem (.2 = 25–49%)",
  "guideEnvQualifiers": "Coding Environmental Factors",
  "guideEnvQualifiersText": "Environmental factors can act as barriers (hindering) or facilitators (supporting). Barriers are coded with a dot, facilitators with a plus sign:",
  "guideBarrierExample": "e150.3 = Building accessibility is a severe barrier",
  "guideFacilitatorExample": "e120+4 = Mobility aids are a complete facilitator",
  "guidePractice1Title": "Example: Knee Surgery (Orthopaedics)",
  "guidePractice1Text": "A 58-year-old patient after knee replacement in rehabilitation:",
  "guidePractice1Code1": "Joint mobility – moderate problem",
  "guidePractice1Code2": "Pain sensation – mild problem",
  "guidePractice1Code3": "Walking – moderate problem",
  "guidePractice1Code4": "Washing oneself – no problem",
  "guidePractice1Code5": "Mobility aids – severe facilitator",
  "guidePractice1Code6": "Health services – moderate facilitator",
  "guidePractice2Title": "Example: Depression (Psychiatry)",
  "guidePractice2Text": "A 34-year-old patient with moderate depressive episode, unable to work for 6 months:",
  "guidePractice2Code1": "Energy and drive – severe problem",
  "guidePractice2Code2": "Emotional functions – severe problem",
  "guidePractice2Code3": "Sleep – moderate problem",
  "guidePractice2Code4": "Handling stress – moderate problem",
  "guidePractice2Code5": "General interpersonal interactions – severe problem",
  "guidePractice2Code6": "Remunerative employment – complete problem",
  "guidePractice2Code7": "Family – severe facilitator",
  "guidePractice2Code8": "Health services – moderate facilitator",
  "guidePractice2Code9": "Societal attitudes – moderate barrier",
  "guidePractice3Title": "Example: Stroke (Neurology)",
  "guidePractice3Text": "A 72-year-old patient 4 weeks after ischaemic stroke with right-sided hemiparesis:",
  "guidePractice3Code1": "Mental functions of language – moderate problem",
  "guidePractice3Code2": "Muscle power – severe problem (right side)",
  "guidePractice3Code3": "Articulation – moderate problem",
  "guidePractice3Code4": "Brain structure – severe impairment",
  "guidePractice3Code5": "Speaking – severe problem",
